sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1919001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutive promotor J23105 and downstream CecropinXJ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shiji Zhao
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Biobrick BBa_K1919001 is a composite part, consisting of constitutive promotor J23105, RBS, TrxA tag, 6xHis tag, thrombin site, S tag, enterkinase site and the coding sequence of antimicrobial peptide CecropinXJ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Two steps were needed in order to obtain BBa_K1919001. Step 1, BBa_K1919000 was inserted into pET32a(+). The primers used for PCR are as following: F: 5'-CCGGGATCCATGAACTTCGCTAAAATCCTGTCTT-3' (BamH I site was added) R: 5'-CCGCTCGAGTTATTATTTACCGATAGCTTTA-3' (Xho I site was added) BamH I/Xho I Double enzymatic cutting was used for both pET32a(+) and BBa_K1919000. Step 2, RBS and 5 downstream tags as well as original CecropinXJ was inserted at the downstream of promotor J23105 with the same procedure as step 1. The primers used for PCR are as following: F: 5'-GCTCTAGAGCGAAGGAGATATACATATGAGCG-3' (Xba I site was added) R: 5'-TGCACTGCAGTGCAGACTAGTCGTTATTGCTCAGCGGTGG-3'(Pst I site was added) Xba I/Pst I double enzymatic cutting was used for PCR product and Spe I/Pst I double enzymatic cutting was used for BBa_J23105. After enzymatic linkage, the construction of BBa_K1919001 was finished. Then this part was added to pSB1C3 backbone.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of constitutive promotor J23105 comes from biobrick BBa_J23105. RBS and 5 downstream tags come from commercial plasmid pET32a(+). The sequence of CecropinXJ comes from biobrick BBa_K1919000.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Wintergree
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Exponential phase dependent wintergreen odor generator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Payne
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part converts salicylic acid into methyl salicylate (a mint-smelling compound) in the exponential phase of cell growth. The part consists of a stationary phase promoter (J45992), connected to an inverter (Q04401) as well as the methyl salicylate protein generator (J45119). This part replaces the defective part J45180, which used the truncated version of the stationary phase promoter (J45993). This part did not function as it was designed due to an imbalance between the strength of the stationary phase promoter and the strength of the promoter in the inverter (R0040).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We needed the full osmY promoter strength to be relatively comparable to the R0040 promoter strength.

The native crtI sequence contains two internal PstI sites. Primers crtImutf1 and crtImutf2 were ordered so that the MABEL protocol (invented for this purpose) could be used to remove these sites. The mutagenic primers were as follows:
* crtImutf1: gtt tac agt aag gtt gcc * crtImutf2: agt aac tct ctg ttt gtg c
